article.headline: Jacksonville 78, North Florida 38
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- Marcus Allen scored 17 points to help Jacksonville rout crosstown rival North Florida 78-38 Thursday night. The Dolphins (7-8, 6-1 Atlantic Sun Conference) remained atop the league standings by winning the seventh of their last 10 games and scoring at least 78 points for the sixth straight game. Jacksonville also won the rebounding battle 45-28. The Ospreys (3-14, 1-6) suffered their second 40-point loss of the season, the first a 76-36 defeat by Clemson on Dec. 16. Jacksonville led 44-23 at halftime, then held North Florida to only 15 points in the second half. The Ospreys shot just 29.8 percent from the field for the game (14 of 47). Ayron Hardy added 12 points for the Dolphins while Lehmon Colbert had 11 and Travis Cohn had 10. Eni Cuka led the Ospreys with 14 points in the game called the SunTrust River City Rumble.
